726938f-a.text:
Jackson Avenue, east side, at Thompson Avenue, showing the Queens County Court House. Directly behind the Court House is the county
jail, seen in part.
March 23, 1932
P.L. Sperr

726937f-a.text:
Jackson Avenue, south side, at Thomson Avenue. Shown is part of the west side of the Queens County Court House and the County Jail (right), seen from Court Square. The Works Progress
Administration is makihg improvements here.
Federal Art Project -- W.P.A.  November, 1936
Photographic Division
